Personal Information Received From the EU:  

Types of Data:  Alticor Inc. (Alticor) and its US-based affiliates may receive a number of different types of data from the EU, including the following:
(a)	employee data;
(b)	distributors, business customers, or suppliers of company; 
(c)	consumers, including but not limited to, purchasers of company products and/or services, consumer research participants, consumers with inquiries about company products and/or services, consumers reporting adverse event reactions to products; and/or
(d)	contractors and consultants

Purposes of data collection and transfer:

The data transferred to Alticor and/or its US-based affiliates from the EU may be used for a variety of purposes, including:
(a)	
(i)  	carrying out a contract with the subject of the data;
(ii)  	providing employee benefits and services; and/or
(iii)	disseminating consumer information, conducting consumer research, and handling consumer inquiries and questions, and conducting consumer promotions;	 

(b)	processing for compliance with a legal obligation;
(c)	processing to carry out legitimate business interests of Alticor and/or any of its affiliates and/or any third parties to whom the data is disclosed; and/or
(d)	processing for purposes consented to by the subjects of the data.
